description: From Tibetan རྫོང (rdzong, “fortress, castle; province, district”).

entries.meaning: A Tibetan building which makes up a prefecture; typically a monastery or fortress.
examples: The rock on which the jong stands must at one time have been lapped by the waters of the lake, but at the present time the Yam-dok tso has retreated so far, that a quashy stretch of vivid green quagmire spreads between the road and the shore.

entries.meaning: Alternative form of djong (“type of sailing ship”)
